{
  "doc_id": "60353",
  "text": "The DNA fragmentation in 180-200 base-pair DNA ladder is a hallmark feature of apoptosis [CITATION_1] . The fragmented DNA can be detected in a single cell using in situ technique such as TUNEL assay [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Data of the present study suggest that NLE induced DNA fragmentation as evidenced by TUNEL positive staining in oocytes that had morphological apoptotic features. These results further confirm our previous finding that NLE induces DNA fragmentation in rat oocytes in vitro [CITATION_7] .",
